- **Moses Montefiore** — Rothschild brother-in-law and
  Jewish philanthropist
- **Lord Palmerston** — British foreign policy interlocutor

#### Anti-Rothschild Literature Indexed

The index reveals extensive coverage of hostile literature
targeting the family — a major theme of the book:

- *Edifying and Curious History of Rothschild I,
  King of the Jews* (Dairnvaell)
- *Ewige Jude, Der* ("The Eternal Jew") — Nazi film
- *Grand Process between Rothschild I, King of the Jews,
  and Satan, Last King of the Impostors*
- *Judgement Passed against Rothschild and Georges
  Dairnvaell* (anonymous)
- *Jud-Süss* — antisemitic film/novel
- *Jews, Kings of the Epoch: A History of Financial
  Feudalism* (Toussenel)
- *Jewish France* (Drumont)
- *Frankfurt Jews and the Mulcting of the People's
  Well-being* ("Germanicus")
- *Myth of the Twentieth Century* (Rosenberg) — Nazi ideologue
- *Imperialism: A Study* (Hobson) — imperialist finance critique
- *New World Order, The* (Robertson) — modern conspiracy lit
- David Icke — modern antisemitic conspiracy theorist

> The range from 1820s French pamphlets through Nazi propaganda
> to 1990s American conspiracy theory shows Ferguson's argument
> that anti-Rothschild mythology is a continuous, mutating
> tradition — not a response to actual Rothschild behavior.

